WEBVTT

00:02.480 --> 00:05.092
WOMAN: Early 60s,
found prone on the sidewalk,

00:05.135 --> 00:07.311
appears to have chest pain,
maybe broken ribs,

00:07.355 --> 00:08.530
possible heart attack.
Did you fall?

00:08.573 --> 00:10.488
She's very disoriented,
hasn't said a thing.

00:10.532 --> 00:12.229
[WEAKLY] Coley?

00:12.273 --> 00:14.492
No,
I'm Dr. Shaun Murphy.

00:15.972 --> 00:17.321
Will you help me,
Coley?

00:19.019 --> 00:21.195
I have to,
it's my job.

00:21.238 --> 00:23.327
She has stridor.
Checking her pulse.

00:25.938 --> 00:27.027
Radial pulse is normal.

00:27.070 --> 00:29.246
But much weaker
in her leg.

00:29.290 --> 00:30.682
She has a descending
thoracic aneurysm.

00:33.033 --> 00:34.817
Page Dr. Melendez
to the O.R.!

00:37.559 --> 00:40.214
I just woke up
on the front campus lawn

00:40.257 --> 00:41.519
covered in blood,

00:41.563 --> 00:43.608
with a skateboard
next to me.

00:43.652 --> 00:45.523
But...
I can't skateboard.

00:45.567 --> 00:46.785
Obviously.

00:46.829 --> 00:48.396
Were you drinking,
Aiden?

00:48.439 --> 00:49.484
Or smoking something?

00:49.527 --> 00:50.659
No to both.

00:52.269 --> 00:54.793
There are actually
college students who abstain.

00:54.837 --> 00:56.273
You are
incredibly lucky...

00:56.317 --> 00:58.058
Half an inch
in any direction,

00:58.101 --> 00:59.059
and you would've
bled out.

01:04.151 --> 01:05.761
Aortic wall's tearing.

01:05.804 --> 01:07.110
Can't expect pristine

01:07.154 --> 01:08.546
in a 60-year-old
possibly homeless woman.

01:08.590 --> 01:09.504
Drop to a 5-0 suture.

01:15.640 --> 01:17.338
Not great, but better.

01:17.381 --> 01:19.862
Let's see if it holds.

01:19.905 --> 01:20.906
Remove proximal clamp.

01:27.130 --> 01:28.262
No leakage.

01:28.305 --> 01:29.480
Let's finish the repair.

01:33.049 --> 01:34.746
Carly broke up with me.

01:37.097 --> 01:38.663
I'm sorry, Shaun.

01:38.707 --> 01:39.795
What happened?

01:39.838 --> 01:41.231
I thought you two
were doing great.

01:41.275 --> 01:43.364
We were.
Then I guess we weren't.

01:43.407 --> 01:44.278
Cross-clamping.

01:46.628 --> 01:48.282
You must really
be hurting?

01:48.325 --> 01:49.979
N-No. I'm fine.

01:51.937 --> 01:53.635
We've all
been through it.

01:53.678 --> 01:55.898
And, trust me, it helps when
you own that you're in pain.

01:55.941 --> 01:58.074
There's nothing for me
to own.

01:58.118 --> 01:59.162
[MONITOR ALARM BLARING]

01:59.206 --> 02:02.078
She's having epistaxis.

02:02.122 --> 02:03.819
Carotid aneurysm rupture,
two French Foley catheters.

02:03.862 --> 02:04.994
Give protamine stat.

02:05.037 --> 02:07.997
♪♪

02:08.040 --> 02:09.999
SHAUN: 68/44.

02:10.042 --> 02:11.566
Holding pressure
on both carotids at the neck.

02:11.609 --> 02:12.958
Inflate.

02:13.002 --> 02:15.091
[ALARM CONTINUES]

02:15.135 --> 02:17.049
41/28.

02:17.093 --> 02:18.399
She's still
bleeding internally.

02:18.442 --> 02:20.227
Okay, four units of PRBCs
and start TXA.

02:20.270 --> 02:22.925
Loading
700 milligrams TXA.

02:22.968 --> 02:24.709
No distal perfusion.

02:24.753 --> 02:26.146
We have to clamp her carotids.
Ten blades.

02:26.189 --> 02:28.365
♪♪

02:33.109 --> 02:34.458
Suction, clamps,
let's go!

02:34.502 --> 02:36.156
♪♪

02:44.294 --> 02:46.078
♪♪

02:47.297 --> 02:49.038
I can't see a thing.

02:49.081 --> 02:50.387
Her blood volume's
on the floor.

02:50.431 --> 02:52.911
♪♪

02:54.391 --> 02:56.306
[ALARM STOPS, FLATLINE]

02:58.047 --> 03:01.224
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

03:02.704 --> 03:04.880
Time of death, 10:22a.m.

03:06.098 --> 03:07.839
[FLATLINE CONTINUES]

03:09.754 --> 03:11.800
♪♪

03:28.469 --> 03:29.905
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

03:30.949 --> 03:32.690
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

03:43.135 --> 03:45.486
Jane shouldn't have died.

03:45.529 --> 03:47.531
Not then,
not like that.

03:47.575 --> 03:48.706
Her carotid blew out.

03:48.750 --> 03:49.968
What am I missing?

03:54.146 --> 03:56.410
Patients die,
Dr. Murphy.

03:56.453 --> 03:57.541
That's something else
we have to own.

04:03.286 --> 04:04.548
Your next patient's waiting
in the E.R.

04:09.379 --> 04:10.859
[DOOR OPENS]

04:10.902 --> 04:12.295
[DOOR CLOSES]

04:15.385 --> 04:16.560
How are you feeling,
Aiden?

04:16.604 --> 04:18.432
Awesome...

04:18.475 --> 04:20.651
Considering
whatever you did to me.

04:20.695 --> 04:21.870
Mm.
Surgery went well.

04:21.913 --> 04:24.264
Hey, I'm alive,
doped up,

04:24.307 --> 04:25.526
talking to two
very attractive doctors.

04:26.744 --> 04:29.051
[CHUCKLES]

04:29.094 --> 04:31.053
[CHUCKLES]
I guess this is what happens

04:31.096 --> 04:33.011
when you mix weed
with my skateboarding skills.

04:33.055 --> 04:34.796
You said
you didn't do drugs.

04:34.839 --> 04:35.927
Or skateboard.

04:35.971 --> 04:37.668
When did I say that?

04:37.712 --> 04:39.496
When we met you
in the E.R.

04:39.540 --> 04:41.585
[CHUCKLES]

04:41.629 --> 04:44.109
I've never seen
you guys before
in my life.

04:44.153 --> 04:46.068
Trust me,
I'd remember.

04:46.111 --> 04:48.200
♪♪

04:51.116 --> 04:52.509
[CHUCKLES]

04:52.553 --> 04:53.554
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

04:57.253 --> 05:00.212
I'd like to order an autopsy
on Jane.

05:00.256 --> 05:01.910
We went over this.

05:01.953 --> 05:04.086
There was nothing suspicious
about her death.

05:04.129 --> 05:07.698
Oh, I was asking
the Chief of Surgery.

05:07.742 --> 05:10.701
I know the case,
and I agree with Dr. Melendez.

05:10.745 --> 05:12.224
I'm not authorizing
an autopsy.

05:12.268 --> 05:14.357
Jane's vascular walls...

05:14.401 --> 05:16.403
It's hard
to lose a patient.

05:16.446 --> 05:18.405
Almost as hard
as losing a girlfriend.

05:18.448 --> 05:22.800
I'm okay, and I don't know why
no one believes me...

05:22.844 --> 05:24.454
Isn't it okay
to be okay?

05:24.498 --> 05:26.151
Not when
something bad happens.

05:26.195 --> 05:28.632
We should feel hurt.

05:28.676 --> 05:30.460
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

05:33.811 --> 05:37.598
If you won't approve
the autopsy,

05:37.641 --> 05:39.774
I'll get it
from Jane's family.

05:39.817 --> 05:41.819
[SIGHS]
Good luck with that.

05:41.863 --> 05:44.866
According to the files,
Jane's last name was Doe.

05:44.909 --> 05:46.781
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

05:46.824 --> 05:49.349
♪♪

06:01.926 --> 06:05.060
Y-You're saying I'm having
some kind of blackouts?

06:05.103 --> 06:08.280
Which could be caused
by head trauma or drug use.

06:08.324 --> 06:09.978
I'm definitely aware
of telling you

06:10.021 --> 06:11.022
that I don't take drugs.

06:13.634 --> 06:15.549
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

06:15.592 --> 06:17.072
I live like a monk.

06:17.115 --> 06:18.987
Sleep, class,
study, repeat.

06:19.030 --> 06:20.075
That's it.

06:20.118 --> 06:21.511
You've also told us
the exact opposite.

06:30.651 --> 06:32.827
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

06:38.354 --> 06:40.182
I need to find
Jane's family

06:40.225 --> 06:42.314
to get their permission
to perform an autopsy.

06:42.358 --> 06:43.707
Dr. Lim wished me luck,

06:43.751 --> 06:46.057
but Jane has no I.D.,
no purse, no phone.

06:46.101 --> 06:48.233
We know absolutely nothing
about her.

06:52.847 --> 06:56.590
Mmm. This should be
interesting to you.

06:56.633 --> 06:58.243
You used to be
a detective.

06:58.287 --> 06:59.636
And now I'm a doctor,

06:59.680 --> 07:01.943
and so are you,
and we both have a new case.

07:01.986 --> 07:03.858
A boring case.

07:03.901 --> 07:05.729
He has gallstones.

07:05.773 --> 07:08.863
♪♪

07:08.906 --> 07:09.994
[DOOR CLOSES]

07:12.562 --> 07:15.043
So, you and Melendez
sneaking around again?

07:18.220 --> 07:20.178
I hear he's back to being
a good mentor.

07:21.397 --> 07:22.485
Apparently,
my complaint changed nothing.

07:24.705 --> 07:25.706
You?

07:28.883 --> 07:30.014
Park said he did it.

07:30.058 --> 07:31.842
Park was lying.

07:31.886 --> 07:34.410
Because he wanted to get you
to focus on work.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.543
Good motive,
bad judge of character.

07:36.586 --> 07:38.066
And you don't like
that Melendez has gone back

07:38.109 --> 07:39.328
to being a good mentor?

07:39.371 --> 07:41.373
I don't like
that he likes you.

07:41.417 --> 07:43.419
I don't like that,
because he likes you,

07:43.463 --> 07:44.899
Shaun, Park, and I
are second-class residents.

07:47.075 --> 07:48.424
[SCOFFS SOFTLY]

07:48.468 --> 07:49.686
For someone
as cynical as you are,

07:49.730 --> 07:51.471
you are shockingly naive.

07:51.514 --> 07:53.081
I'll tell you
what you did.

07:53.124 --> 07:54.909
You threw a bomb
because you felt slighted.

07:54.952 --> 07:57.346
You made Melendez
doubt himself,

07:57.389 --> 07:58.739
doubt his judgment.

07:58.782 --> 08:02.133
You made him resent
you, Park, Shaun, and me.

08:04.396 --> 08:05.572
I like to think
it's that easy

08:05.615 --> 08:07.138
to change the status quo.

08:07.182 --> 08:08.749
But I am pretty naive.

08:13.188 --> 08:15.538
I am with Dr. B on this.

08:16.757 --> 08:18.323
[SIGHS] Sorry.

08:18.367 --> 08:20.108
Office politics.

08:20.151 --> 08:22.502
Thought you were asleep.

08:22.545 --> 08:24.808
Watching brain waves
can't be too thrilling.

08:24.852 --> 08:26.810
Not when they're
as normal as yours.

08:26.854 --> 08:27.942
Hmm.

08:27.985 --> 08:29.813
Except these delta waves.

08:29.857 --> 08:31.467
♪♪

08:31.511 --> 08:33.164
They mean
you're still asleep.

08:33.208 --> 08:35.645
♪♪

08:44.828 --> 08:48.353
Not planning on doing
any cutting, I hope.

08:48.397 --> 08:52.227
Jane had a knee replacement
using an LCS system,

08:52.270 --> 08:54.011
which means
it's at least 30 years old.

08:54.055 --> 08:56.057
She also had
an abnormal number

08:56.100 --> 08:58.538
of cavities, crowns,
and implants.

08:59.626 --> 09:00.931
These are clues,
right?

09:04.195 --> 09:07.459
I don't think this is about
you losing a patient.

09:07.503 --> 09:09.418
I think you're
distracting yourself.

09:10.462 --> 09:11.812
You don't want
to let Jane go

09:11.855 --> 09:13.683
because you don't want
to let Carly go.

09:20.908 --> 09:21.909
Hmm.

09:25.826 --> 09:26.914
What?

09:30.526 --> 09:31.832
You're a doctor now.

09:31.875 --> 09:33.747
You won't
find it interesting.

09:36.837 --> 09:37.838
Hmm.

09:51.155 --> 09:52.592
PARK: A hummingbird.

09:54.376 --> 09:55.682
Am I right?

09:58.206 --> 10:00.817
PARK: The police
keep a database
of all distinguishing marks.

10:00.861 --> 10:02.645
Jane Doe, homeless...

10:02.689 --> 10:04.821
There's no way
she was never in the system...

10:04.865 --> 10:06.649
How's Mr. Ginley?

10:06.693 --> 10:09.304
Your gallbladder case
you should be working on?

10:09.347 --> 10:11.959
Uh, we confirmed
the presence of gallstones

10:12.002 --> 10:13.787
and have scheduled
a cholecystectomy.

10:13.830 --> 10:16.093
It's a very simple case
and requires no work.

10:18.226 --> 10:19.706
With that attitude,

10:19.749 --> 10:21.882
you could end up sending
another patient to the morgue.

10:24.406 --> 10:25.625
Focus on the living.

10:29.716 --> 10:31.587
He's right.
We need to bail on this.

10:35.504 --> 10:36.723
Hey, Shaun.

10:37.245 --> 10:39.334
[SIGHS]

10:39.377 --> 10:42.642
You and Carly shared
a lot of firsts.

10:42.685 --> 10:44.295
That must make it harder
to move on.

10:46.602 --> 10:48.735
I had a lot of firsts
with Lea, too.

10:48.778 --> 10:50.824
Yeah, you did.
And you moved on.

10:54.088 --> 10:55.219
Didn't you?

10:58.832 --> 11:01.008
How do you move on?

11:01.051 --> 11:04.620
♪♪

11:08.145 --> 11:09.277
Hmm.

11:09.320 --> 11:12.541
[CELLPHONE VIBRATING]

11:12.584 --> 11:14.195
[SIGHS]

11:14.238 --> 11:16.676
♪♪

11:16.719 --> 11:18.547
[KEYBOARD CLACKS]

11:18.590 --> 11:21.506
[VIBRATING CONTINUES]

11:21.550 --> 11:23.378
Hey, Kenny,
I need a name.

11:26.076 --> 11:27.556
We need to keep this
on the DL.

11:27.599 --> 11:29.427
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

11:29.471 --> 11:31.342
We're going undercover.

11:33.344 --> 11:34.911
Causes of sleepwalking
run the gamut

11:34.955 --> 11:36.347
from the serious,

11:36.391 --> 11:38.436
like MS, encephalitis,
and brain tumors,

11:38.480 --> 11:41.004
to the mundane,
like alcohol and drug use,

11:41.048 --> 11:42.963
poor sleep hygiene,
and stress.

11:43.006 --> 11:44.965
Problem is,
to rule some of those out,

11:45.008 --> 11:46.749
we need
a full patient history,

11:46.793 --> 11:49.447
but AsleepAiden and AwakeAiden
each have their own story.

11:49.491 --> 11:51.449
So interview them
both.

11:51.493 --> 11:53.800
Take a medical history from
a patient when they're asleep?

11:53.843 --> 11:55.627
I've never heard of
a lying sleepwalker.

11:58.282 --> 12:00.371
I got to go.

12:00.415 --> 12:01.590
♪♪

12:01.633 --> 12:03.374
Hey!

12:03.418 --> 12:05.550
♪♪

12:09.076 --> 12:10.642
Stress?

12:10.686 --> 12:12.470
I have to maintain
a 4.2 GPA.

12:12.514 --> 12:14.559
W-What do you think?

12:14.603 --> 12:16.474
[CHUCKLES]

12:16.518 --> 12:19.042
You have to care
about something
to be stressed, don't you?

12:19.086 --> 12:21.828
And since I'm getting a 4.2
without trying...

12:21.871 --> 12:22.959
Maybe a glass of wine
at a party.

12:23.003 --> 12:24.352
I just microdose...

12:24.395 --> 12:27.268
You know, whenever
I'm not macrodosing.

12:27.311 --> 12:30.053
Do you nap,
exercise before bedtime?

12:30.097 --> 12:31.838
I never nap,
I work out five days a week...

12:31.881 --> 12:33.491
Never too close to bedtime,
which is midnight,

12:33.535 --> 12:34.841
12:30 at the latest.

12:34.884 --> 12:38.018
I am surrounded
by 5,000 women.

12:38.061 --> 12:41.064
Yes,
right before bedtime.

12:41.108 --> 12:44.024
♪♪

12:44.067 --> 12:46.156
That explains the headaches
I've been waking up with.

12:48.942 --> 12:50.378
I never thought
that they were hangovers.

12:54.295 --> 12:56.819
He's a Cro-Magnon.

12:58.560 --> 13:00.736
He's not me.

13:00.780 --> 13:03.521
♪♪

13:03.565 --> 13:05.436
He can't be.

13:05.480 --> 13:07.917
♪♪

13:12.574 --> 13:14.794
[SLIDE CLICKS]

13:14.837 --> 13:17.013
SHAUN:
Maribel Ventane.

13:17.057 --> 13:19.233
[SLIDE CLICKS]

13:19.276 --> 13:21.017
♪♪

13:21.061 --> 13:24.064
"Sharing the Spirit.

13:24.107 --> 13:26.806
"Marco, Maribel, and
their 5-year-old son, Jules,

13:26.849 --> 13:28.633
"open their doors
to host

13:28.677 --> 13:31.767
"the fourth annual fundraiser
'Friends in Need.'"

13:31.811 --> 13:33.856
"Maribel Ventane, 33,

13:33.900 --> 13:35.815
"was one jump away
from a first-place ribbon."

13:35.858 --> 13:37.077
Blah, blah, blah.

13:37.120 --> 13:39.949
"She suffered
severe orthopedic injuries."

13:39.993 --> 13:41.777
"After two years
in family court,

13:41.821 --> 13:43.692
"Maribel Ventane, 36,

13:43.735 --> 13:45.781
"and ex-husband
Marco Ventane, 43"...

13:45.825 --> 13:47.087
Blah, blah, blah.

13:47.130 --> 13:49.524
"Mr. Ventane was given
full custody

13:49.567 --> 13:51.787
"of their 11-year-old son,
Jules."

13:51.831 --> 13:54.355
"Marco Ventane, 63,
passed away in his home.

13:54.398 --> 13:56.879
"He is survived by his son,
Jules Ventane, 32."

13:58.533 --> 14:00.404
[KEYBOARD CLICKING]

14:00.448 --> 14:01.405
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

14:01.449 --> 14:02.711
I found him.

14:02.754 --> 14:04.974
♪♪

14:12.547 --> 14:15.028
♪♪

14:21.773 --> 14:22.905
[ENGINE SHUTS OFF]

14:33.133 --> 14:35.178
Are you Jules Ventane?

14:35.222 --> 14:36.527
Yes.

14:36.571 --> 14:38.834
I'm Dr. Shaun Murphy,

14:38.878 --> 14:40.792
and I recently treated
your mother, Maribel.

14:40.836 --> 14:42.533
She died
on the operating table.

14:42.577 --> 14:44.448
I would like your permission
to do an autopsy.

14:44.492 --> 14:46.015
We're very sorry
for your loss.

14:46.059 --> 14:48.235
She came in with
a ruptured aortic aneurysm,

14:48.278 --> 14:50.541
and there wasn't much
we could do.

14:50.585 --> 14:53.153
But we would like
to be absolutely certain

14:53.196 --> 14:54.806
about her
cause of death.

14:58.419 --> 15:00.073
I don't care
how she died.

15:01.378 --> 15:04.904
♪♪

15:14.304 --> 15:18.004
Remember we talked about
moving on?

15:18.047 --> 15:19.962
This is the time
to do that.

15:20.006 --> 15:22.922
♪♪

15:33.933 --> 15:35.151
Where do we stand
with the Aidens?

15:35.195 --> 15:36.500
Between the two alters,

15:36.544 --> 15:38.807
they engage in just about
every single behavior.

15:38.850 --> 15:40.983
So, we go back
to Dr. Lim's list.

15:41.027 --> 15:43.594
Maybe we should be looking at
paraneoplastic syndromes.

15:43.638 --> 15:45.901
DR. MELENDEZ:
May want to consider
psychiatric issues...

15:45.945 --> 15:47.816
Could be having psychotic
or dissociative episodes.

15:49.339 --> 15:50.993
I have a fair amount
of personal experience

15:51.037 --> 15:53.256
with people
with psychiatric issues.

15:53.300 --> 15:55.824
If he had psychosis,
I'd have picked up on it.

15:57.782 --> 15:59.871
How about thyrotoxicosis?

15:59.915 --> 16:02.309
No irritability,
agitation.

16:02.352 --> 16:04.267
Paraneoplastic syndromes
trigger a loss
of coordination,

16:04.311 --> 16:05.616
which could have caused...

16:05.660 --> 16:07.314
Actually,
our personal experiences

16:07.357 --> 16:08.968
make us less effective
in spotting symptoms.

16:09.881 --> 16:11.274
You know
I always make an effort

16:11.318 --> 16:13.015
to be as objective
as possible.

16:13.059 --> 16:15.539
Well,
you're not this time.

16:15.583 --> 16:18.151
The vast majority of cases
of paraneoplastic syndromes

16:18.194 --> 16:20.109
present with antibodies.

16:20.153 --> 16:22.024
His labs show
a normal serum panel.

16:22.068 --> 16:24.157
The "vast majority"
of all diseases

16:24.200 --> 16:26.724
don't present with competing
entities day and night.

16:26.768 --> 16:29.292
I'm just giving an idea.
No,
you're undermining mine.

16:29.336 --> 16:31.555
Fine. Your idea's brilliant.
Go waste your time on it.

16:31.599 --> 16:33.122
Thank you both.

16:33.166 --> 16:34.732
Get an MRI to rule out
brain tumors and MS,

16:34.776 --> 16:36.560
an LP for encephalitis,

16:36.604 --> 16:40.738
and a CSF panel to check for
paraneoplastic syndromes.

16:40.782 --> 16:42.479
And a psych consult.

16:42.523 --> 16:46.222
♪♪

16:50.705 --> 16:53.055
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

16:53.099 --> 16:55.057
[SIGHS]

16:55.101 --> 16:57.190
[CELLPHONE SWISHES]

16:57.233 --> 17:00.280
♪♪

17:03.587 --> 17:04.588
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

17:04.632 --> 17:07.678
♪♪

17:07.722 --> 17:09.593
No.

17:09.637 --> 17:12.248
♪♪

17:22.302 --> 17:23.651
Hi.

17:26.567 --> 17:29.004
I'm Dr. Lim.

17:29.048 --> 17:31.485
And you are?
Trinity.

17:32.834 --> 17:34.140
Where are your parents?

17:36.142 --> 17:37.708
My mother's
in the maternity ward.

17:37.752 --> 17:39.754
She's having a baby?

17:39.797 --> 17:41.582
Already did.
A girl.

17:41.625 --> 17:42.800
Wonderful.

17:42.844 --> 17:45.151
So, why the wandering?

17:45.194 --> 17:47.675
My mom sent me
to the cafeteria
to get a snack,

17:47.718 --> 17:50.025
but I got lost.

17:50.069 --> 17:52.114
[SIGHS]
Three times?

17:58.816 --> 18:02.342
Hey, Lucy.
We're looking for, um...

18:02.385 --> 18:03.343
[SIGHS] Trinity!

18:05.127 --> 18:08.478
[SIGHS]
Please call security.

18:08.522 --> 18:10.785
♪♪

18:10.828 --> 18:13.266
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

18:15.311 --> 18:17.748
[GEARSHIFT CLICKS,
ENGINE REVS]

18:17.792 --> 18:22.840
♪♪

18:28.150 --> 18:29.325
Stop the car.

18:29.369 --> 18:30.587
No.

18:30.631 --> 18:31.893
Yes.

18:31.936 --> 18:33.895
Shaun! Shaun!

18:33.938 --> 18:35.157
I need your permission!

18:35.201 --> 18:36.637
Don't do this, Shaun!
No!

18:36.680 --> 18:37.812
I need your permission!
Let it go, Shaun!

18:37.855 --> 18:39.509
It can't be over!

18:39.553 --> 18:41.076
It can't be over!
It's over!
You have to let Carly go!

18:41.120 --> 18:42.425
No! No!
You have to let Carly go!

18:42.469 --> 18:43.731
No!
You have to let Carly go!

18:43.774 --> 18:45.211
It's not about Carly!

18:45.254 --> 18:46.603
Well, it's not about this,
either!

18:46.647 --> 18:48.388
It is not about Carly!
He's calling the police!

18:48.431 --> 18:50.085
No!
Open the door!You'll get arrested!

18:50.129 --> 18:51.565
[MUFFLED] Open the door!

18:51.608 --> 18:53.001
[MUFFLED] Shaun,
he's calling the police!

18:53.044 --> 18:55.786
Come here! Shaun!
No! Open the...

19:12.890 --> 19:14.153
Oh, my God.

19:14.196 --> 19:16.024
Shaun,
are you okay?

19:16.067 --> 19:18.418
It was bad.
I missed my surgery.

19:18.461 --> 19:19.941
Well,
don't worry about that.

19:19.984 --> 19:22.248
Park's there.
Everything there is fine.

19:22.291 --> 19:23.640
Will I have to
go back to jail?

19:23.684 --> 19:26.339
No. No.

19:26.382 --> 19:28.341
It's a good thing
you were with an ex-cop.

19:28.384 --> 19:30.908
The guy's not gonna
press any charges,

19:30.952 --> 19:33.302
but you're not allowed to be
anywhere near him ever again.

19:36.087 --> 19:37.350
Here.

19:37.393 --> 19:39.221
Let's get out of here,
huh?

19:43.878 --> 19:46.315
Park says that you are upset
about Carly.

19:47.273 --> 19:49.884
Everyone keeps
telling me that,

19:49.927 --> 19:52.626
but I am not upset
about Carly,

19:52.669 --> 19:54.193
and they need to stop.

19:54.236 --> 19:56.282
Okay,
so, this isn't about Carly.

19:56.325 --> 19:59.023
I wish Carly
didn't break up with me.

19:59.502 --> 20:01.504
But she did.

20:02.549 --> 20:05.378
And now I have to do
what she said.

20:05.421 --> 20:06.857
What do you mean
you have to do what she said?

20:06.901 --> 20:08.076
She doesn't get
to dictate to you.

20:08.119 --> 20:10.209
She told me to tell Lea
I love her.

20:11.688 --> 20:14.343
♪♪

20:16.519 --> 20:18.304
Oh.

20:18.347 --> 20:21.437
♪♪

20:22.264 --> 20:23.744
O-Oh.

20:23.787 --> 20:25.398
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

20:25.441 --> 20:28.139
♪♪

20:28.183 --> 20:30.185
And you're afraid
of what might happen

20:30.229 --> 20:32.492
if you told Lea
the truth?

20:32.883 --> 20:34.363
♪♪

20:35.799 --> 20:38.280
If I tell her
I love her

20:39.586 --> 20:41.936
and she tells me
she doesn't,

20:43.372 --> 20:45.505
then I can't be
her boyfriend.

20:46.593 --> 20:48.290
And even worse, I...

20:49.857 --> 20:53.339
I don't think I can be
her friend, either.

20:53.382 --> 20:56.342
♪♪

21:08.223 --> 21:10.530
And what if Lea
were to say...

21:11.400 --> 21:12.575
[SIGHS]

21:12.619 --> 21:15.926
..."You know what, Shaun?
I love you, too"?

21:15.970 --> 21:18.146
♪♪

21:19.626 --> 21:22.281
Hmm.

21:22.324 --> 21:25.371
♪♪

21:26.720 --> 21:28.896
AIDEN:
Pretty disturbing,

21:28.939 --> 21:32.203
having this weird personality
creeping out of me.

21:32.247 --> 21:35.990
Does he represent something
I'm suppressing

21:36.033 --> 21:37.992
and need to express

21:38.035 --> 21:40.516
or something I need
to bury forever?

21:42.518 --> 21:45.608
If it's any consolation,
I kind of like him.

21:45.652 --> 21:47.828
I think he's just trying
to enjoy himself.

21:47.871 --> 21:49.220
Except he's sabotaging

21:49.264 --> 21:51.266
all the hard work
of his waking self.

21:51.310 --> 21:53.399
It's not sabotage.
It's just a part of who he is.

21:53.442 --> 21:55.531
Some parts
of who we are suck.

22:01.145 --> 22:02.973
I'm sorry.

22:03.017 --> 22:04.235
I shouldn't have ratted
on you and Melendez.

22:04.279 --> 22:05.585
I screwed things up.

22:07.587 --> 22:09.893
But this guy needs a drink
every now and again.

22:09.937 --> 22:12.026
[COMPUTER BEEPS]

22:12.853 --> 22:13.767
You see that?

22:13.810 --> 22:15.986
Yeah.

22:16.030 --> 22:17.553
[CHUCKLES]

22:19.033 --> 22:20.600
You have
an arachnoid cyst

22:20.643 --> 22:22.341
compressing your hypothalamus,
Aiden.

22:22.384 --> 22:24.952
We basically
just need to drain it.

22:24.995 --> 22:26.519
[MRI MACHINE PULSING]

22:28.259 --> 22:30.305
W-Will it kill me
if you don't?

22:35.571 --> 22:36.355
DR. ANDREWS:
He knows the risks?

22:36.398 --> 22:38.444
CLAIRE: He knows
it won't kill him,

22:38.487 --> 22:40.271
which is enough
for Jekyll

22:40.315 --> 22:42.883
to decide
to keep Hyde alive.

22:42.926 --> 22:44.798
What if we ask Hyde?

22:46.147 --> 22:47.670
I'm pretty sure
consent needs to be

22:47.714 --> 22:49.759
informed, voluntary,
and conscious.

22:49.803 --> 22:51.848
It also doesn't matter.
AsleepAiden's a hedonist.

22:51.892 --> 22:54.285
He's not gonna make a decision
against his interest

22:54.329 --> 22:55.417
just to help
his alter.

22:55.461 --> 22:57.767
Maybe he cares
more than you think.

23:00.901 --> 23:02.424
Okay.

23:06.689 --> 23:07.995
Dr. Lim?

23:09.779 --> 23:11.999
Thank you.

23:12.042 --> 23:12.826
Trinity,
have a seat.

23:20.486 --> 23:22.401
There's no one
in our maternity ward

23:22.444 --> 23:23.793
with a daughter
named Trinity.

23:25.578 --> 23:29.625
So, I'm gonna need
some information,

23:29.669 --> 23:31.932
and it will be
much more efficient

23:31.975 --> 23:32.846
if it's the truth.

23:33.368 --> 23:35.196
[PAPER RUSTLES]

23:35.239 --> 23:36.197
First and last name.

23:36.240 --> 23:37.633
Trinity.

23:37.677 --> 23:38.634
Mm-hmm.
Last name?

23:43.596 --> 23:45.336
Okay.

23:45.380 --> 23:46.686
Will you at least
tell me

23:46.729 --> 23:48.383
what you're doing
in this hospital?

23:50.516 --> 23:53.562
I just wanted
to meet you again.

23:59.307 --> 24:00.874
♪♪

24:03.093 --> 24:07.750
Someone left a baby girl
at the E.R.
about eight years ago,

24:07.794 --> 24:09.491
on Trinity Sunday.

24:09.535 --> 24:11.406
♪♪

24:13.582 --> 24:15.845
You were so tiny,

24:16.759 --> 24:19.632
so sick,
and so helpless.

24:20.415 --> 24:22.112
♪♪

24:22.156 --> 24:24.027
Killed me
not to take you home.

24:26.900 --> 24:30.469
But look at you now,
so strong and healthy.

24:30.512 --> 24:32.993
And fast. [CHUCKLES]

24:33.036 --> 24:35.561
♪♪

24:35.604 --> 24:36.692
You know
we need to call your mother

24:36.736 --> 24:38.259
and let her know
where you are.

24:38.302 --> 24:39.913
That you're okay.

24:40.957 --> 24:42.045
You know her number?

24:42.089 --> 24:44.526
♪♪

24:44.570 --> 24:45.875
Yes, but...

24:47.964 --> 24:49.923
But?

24:49.966 --> 24:51.707
Can you adopt me?

24:52.665 --> 24:57.452
♪♪

25:09.159 --> 25:10.900
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

25:10.944 --> 25:14.338
♪♪

25:24.044 --> 25:25.349
Shaunie.

25:26.481 --> 25:27.656
You poor thing.

25:27.700 --> 25:30.137
I'm so sorry
about you and Carly.

25:33.662 --> 25:37.797
I want to tell you
how I feel.

25:41.235 --> 25:42.976
[SIGHS]

25:55.292 --> 25:57.512
[SIGHS]

25:58.469 --> 26:00.123
I know
you're hurting.

26:01.995 --> 26:04.737
Carly made
a huge mistake.

26:07.087 --> 26:09.611
You're a wonderful man,
Shaun.

26:10.743 --> 26:14.877
Maybe the most wonderful man
I've ever met.

26:14.921 --> 26:18.794
♪♪

26:18.838 --> 26:20.187
Lea?

26:20.230 --> 26:21.492
Yeah, Shaun?

26:27.150 --> 26:29.283
[SIGHS]

26:38.074 --> 26:40.642
TRINITY: I found that
in my mother's drawer.

26:40.686 --> 26:42.862
Does she know
you're here?

26:42.905 --> 26:44.515
She's been
in Campbell Memorial

26:44.559 --> 26:46.300
for the last two days.

26:46.343 --> 26:48.171
She thinks
I've been in school

26:48.215 --> 26:49.564
and at a friend's.

26:49.608 --> 26:50.957
As long
as I'm home by 6:00,

26:51.000 --> 26:53.046
no one knows
the difference.

26:53.089 --> 26:55.526
Mmm, well,
it's past that.

26:55.570 --> 26:57.746
I'm sure she's worried.

26:57.790 --> 26:59.661
She has a new daughter.

27:02.359 --> 27:05.188
It's hard to share your mom,
isn't it?

27:09.540 --> 27:12.021
If she loves your sister
with all her heart,

27:12.065 --> 27:14.633
it doesn't feel like
it'd leave much room for you.

27:20.203 --> 27:22.728
Do you love your mom
with all your heart?

27:24.425 --> 27:25.818
How about your dad?

27:25.861 --> 27:27.515
You love him
with all your heart, too?

27:27.558 --> 27:30.300
But that doesn't
seem possible, does it?

27:30.344 --> 27:33.564
♪♪

27:33.608 --> 27:36.132
Hearts are
amazing things.

27:37.612 --> 27:41.529
I've held one in my hands
many times.

27:41.572 --> 27:43.487
You'd never know it
by looking at them,

27:43.531 --> 27:49.842
but somehow, they have
all the room we need.

28:03.159 --> 28:05.684
Dr. B.

28:05.727 --> 28:07.511
Please tell me
you're single.

28:07.555 --> 28:08.948
[SIGHS]

28:12.734 --> 28:14.040
[LIGHT SWITCH CLICKS]

28:18.218 --> 28:20.394
You have a cyst
in your brain.

28:20.437 --> 28:23.049
If we leave it as is,
it could expose you

28:23.092 --> 28:25.529
to considerable
neurological complications,

28:25.573 --> 28:26.792
potential visual loss,

28:26.835 --> 28:29.185
endocrine abnormalities,
depression.

28:29.229 --> 28:32.449
But if we drain
and treat the cyst,

28:32.493 --> 28:36.323
there should be
no complications.

28:36.366 --> 28:39.456
Including sleepwalking.

28:39.500 --> 28:41.197
[CHUCKLES]

28:46.072 --> 28:47.900
The Professor already
rejected treatment?

28:50.990 --> 28:53.253
So you're asking
the Frat Boy

28:53.296 --> 28:55.821
to fall on his sword
for him?

28:55.864 --> 28:58.693
I think the Frat Boy

28:58.737 --> 29:00.390
is more than
just a Frat Boy.

29:02.392 --> 29:03.959
We're all complicated.

29:04.003 --> 29:07.702
We're all sometimes
superficial, selfish jerks.

29:07.746 --> 29:09.530
But we're also
capable of sacrifice.

29:09.573 --> 29:12.838
♪♪

29:13.882 --> 29:16.885
I think you live in him

29:16.929 --> 29:18.800
the same way
he lives in you.

29:18.844 --> 29:21.847
And that won't change,

29:21.890 --> 29:24.110
no matter what decision
you make.

29:24.153 --> 29:26.634
[SIGHS]

29:26.677 --> 29:28.723
♪♪

29:28.767 --> 29:30.638
[LOUD KNOCK ON DOOR]

29:34.773 --> 29:35.904
Shaun.

29:37.776 --> 29:39.342
Maribel died.

29:39.386 --> 29:42.432
I think she had
polycystic kidney disease,

29:42.476 --> 29:44.608
which is associated with
dilation of the arteries,

29:44.652 --> 29:46.610
which results in
weakened vascular walls,

29:46.654 --> 29:49.265
which in turn contributes
to the formation of aneurysms.

29:49.309 --> 29:51.877
I need to do an autopsy.

29:52.921 --> 29:54.662
Dr. Melendez...

29:54.705 --> 29:56.838
Didn't approve.
Dr. Lim didn't approve.

29:56.882 --> 29:59.101
The family said no.
So, what can I...

29:59.145 --> 30:01.930
You're the head
of pathology.

30:01.974 --> 30:04.933
Shaun,
I'm not going to...

30:04.977 --> 30:08.894
I can't do
what you told me I should do.

30:10.939 --> 30:13.637
Until I solve
this distraction.

30:15.683 --> 30:18.207
♪♪

30:25.214 --> 30:28.087
♪♪

30:28.130 --> 30:30.306
No sign
of polycystic kidney disease.

30:39.968 --> 30:41.448
[INSTRUMENT CLACKS]

30:49.325 --> 30:52.067
I know that this break-up
has been hard on you.

30:52.111 --> 30:53.895
It's been hard on me, too.

30:56.724 --> 30:58.857
But I know what I saw
between you and Lea.

30:58.900 --> 31:01.772
♪♪

31:07.430 --> 31:11.304
I did see something,
didn't I?

31:11.347 --> 31:13.654
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

31:20.400 --> 31:21.705
I love you, Carly.

31:23.142 --> 31:25.361
♪♪

31:26.580 --> 31:29.148
But you were right.
I love Lea more.

31:29.191 --> 31:32.760
♪♪

31:33.195 --> 31:34.327
Okay.

31:38.461 --> 31:39.941
So...

31:42.204 --> 31:43.902
You know you have to
tell her, right?

31:43.945 --> 31:47.296
♪♪

31:47.340 --> 31:49.646
I'm scared.

31:49.690 --> 31:51.866
I know.

31:51.910 --> 31:54.173
♪♪

31:57.002 --> 31:58.917
But look at how far
you've come with me...

32:01.397 --> 32:03.704
How scared you were.

32:03.747 --> 32:05.706
[SIGHS]

32:05.749 --> 32:08.187
How brave you were.

32:25.639 --> 32:27.467
I have to go.

32:28.772 --> 32:30.949
[GLOVES SNAP]

32:30.992 --> 32:34.039
♪♪

32:39.000 --> 32:40.784
Thank you, Carly.

32:40.828 --> 32:44.136
♪♪

32:58.585 --> 33:02.197
♪♪

33:16.255 --> 33:18.039
[SIGHS]

33:18.083 --> 33:22.261
If you're watching this,
it means I'm dead.

33:22.304 --> 33:23.871
[CHUCKLES]

33:23.914 --> 33:26.830
And you're waking up from a surgery

33:26.874 --> 33:29.094
you think you didn't consent to,

33:29.137 --> 33:32.662
but I hereby proffer
my full and informed consent

33:32.706 --> 33:34.447
to said surgical procedure.

33:34.490 --> 33:40.627
Signed Aiden...
Michael... Porter.

33:40.670 --> 33:41.845
The second.

33:44.370 --> 33:45.849
[SCOFFS SOFTLY]

33:45.893 --> 33:48.374
Uh, just one... One more thing.

33:48.417 --> 33:50.332
♪♪

33:52.639 --> 33:54.249
My advice...

33:54.293 --> 33:56.034
♪♪

33:57.948 --> 33:59.559
...is to try
to chillax a little.

34:01.169 --> 34:02.823
Neither of us is perfect.

34:03.563 --> 34:06.305
But... We're okay.

34:07.654 --> 34:11.310
♪♪

34:13.877 --> 34:15.923
We are gonna be...

34:18.273 --> 34:19.448
...okay.

34:19.492 --> 34:21.842
♪♪

34:21.885 --> 34:26.368
And[SIGHS] that girl

34:26.412 --> 34:28.805
who sits in front of you
in Advanced Calculus,

34:28.849 --> 34:33.201
her name is Staci with an "i," and she likes you.

34:34.768 --> 34:36.378
Way more than she likes me.

34:36.422 --> 34:39.077
♪♪

34:43.603 --> 34:45.866
Peace out, Professor.

34:45.909 --> 34:48.347
♪♪

34:49.826 --> 34:52.307
[SIGHS, SNIFFLES]

34:52.351 --> 34:55.354
♪♪

35:04.624 --> 35:06.060
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

35:06.104 --> 35:07.148
You're kidding me,
right?

35:07.192 --> 35:08.584
SHAUN: I know
why your mother died.

35:08.628 --> 35:10.325
And I said
I didn't care.

35:10.369 --> 35:12.110
When I examined
her liver,

35:12.153 --> 35:14.503
I found three aneurysms
in her hepatic artery,

35:14.547 --> 35:16.418
which is very unusual
and made me realize

35:16.462 --> 35:18.594
she has Vascular
Ehlers-Danlos syndrome.

35:18.638 --> 35:20.030
It's a very rare disease

35:20.074 --> 35:22.772
that often goes undiagnosed
and can be fatal.

35:22.816 --> 35:24.078
Are you really gonna make me
call the police again?

35:24.122 --> 35:25.427
It's hereditary.

35:25.471 --> 35:27.125
No, I don't want
to get arrested again,

35:27.168 --> 35:28.648
but do you have
an excess of cavities?

35:28.691 --> 35:30.780
You might have
inherited Vascular
Ehlers-Danlos syndrome

35:30.824 --> 35:32.173
from your mother,

35:32.217 --> 35:33.783
and your life
could be in danger.

35:33.827 --> 35:35.394
But its symptoms
can be treated.

35:38.832 --> 35:39.789
Okay, goodbye.

35:42.836 --> 35:44.272
[DOOR OPENS]

35:48.058 --> 35:50.539
So, that's all I got
from my mother?

35:52.759 --> 35:54.543
A potentially
deadly disease?

36:02.290 --> 36:06.381
Did your mother
ever call you "Coley"?

36:10.037 --> 36:11.430
Yeah.

36:14.084 --> 36:16.391
Short for "colibri,"

36:17.871 --> 36:19.394
the French word
for hummingbird.

36:21.396 --> 36:24.007
She said I would
flit around the house,

36:25.183 --> 36:27.446
always going from one thing
to another.

36:33.452 --> 36:38.239
She had a hummingbird
tattooed on her body.

36:41.721 --> 36:44.680
And "Coley"
was the last word she said.

36:54.037 --> 36:56.910
She loved you.

36:59.434 --> 37:04.483
M-Maybe she was just afraid
to tell you.

37:04.526 --> 37:07.921
♪♪

37:22.065 --> 37:24.024
[SIGHS]

37:24.067 --> 37:26.809
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

37:26.853 --> 37:28.594
[PINS CLATTER]

37:28.637 --> 37:31.727
♪♪

37:36.341 --> 37:38.125
Morgan buy the fight?
[SIGHS]

37:38.168 --> 37:39.866
Is it weird
how hard we have to work

37:39.909 --> 37:41.563
to hide
a platonic friendship?

37:41.607 --> 37:43.913
Very.
But it's worth it.

37:43.957 --> 37:46.089
♪♪

37:50.877 --> 37:54.402
♪♪

38:25.738 --> 38:28.001
♪♪

38:32.397 --> 38:34.442
[SNIFFLES]

38:47.673 --> 38:50.806
♪♪

38:54.636 --> 38:56.769
[CELLPHONE CLICKING]

38:56.812 --> 38:58.771
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

38:58.814 --> 39:01.774
♪♪

39:01.817 --> 39:03.471
Hi, Mom.

39:04.907 --> 39:06.605
Shaun?

39:21.097 --> 39:22.708
What's up, Shaunie?

39:28.409 --> 39:29.976
Shaun.

39:31.412 --> 39:32.674
Please.

39:32.718 --> 39:34.633
Talk to me.

39:42.858 --> 39:44.207
I love you, Lea.

39:50.039 --> 39:52.651
I want to be
your boyfriend.

39:58.352 --> 40:00.006
I love you, too.

40:08.144 --> 40:09.232
[SMACKS LIPS,
INHALES DEEPLY]

40:09.276 --> 40:11.278
But [SIGHS]

40:13.715 --> 40:16.022
you know me.

40:16.065 --> 40:21.549
I am selfish,
and I am so, so needy.

40:22.768 --> 40:23.899
I-I'm...

40:24.987 --> 40:26.641
I mean,
listen to me right now.

40:26.685 --> 40:28.382
I can't even put
a complete sentence together.

40:28.426 --> 40:30.079
I am a...
I'm a total mess.

40:31.603 --> 40:33.518
[VOICE BREAKING] How?

40:33.561 --> 40:36.825
How am I supposed to,
you know,

40:36.869 --> 40:38.784
just lay all of that
on you?

40:43.702 --> 40:49.447
Why do you think
I can't handle

40:49.490 --> 40:53.102
your selfishness,
neediness, and messiness?

40:53.146 --> 40:54.713
I think I can.

40:57.106 --> 40:58.717
It's just...

41:00.240 --> 41:02.938
I'm a challenge
for anyone...

41:02.982 --> 41:04.331
And you're...

41:05.114 --> 41:06.333
You.

41:07.377 --> 41:08.944
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

41:08.988 --> 41:12.687
And I just know
it would be too hard for you.

41:13.645 --> 41:16.299
You need things
a certain way.

41:16.343 --> 41:18.867
You work
in a certain way and...

41:20.869 --> 41:22.654
[SIGHS]

41:25.961 --> 41:27.354
Because...

41:28.224 --> 41:29.748
I have autism?

41:32.664 --> 41:34.100
You

41:36.494 --> 41:39.235
don't want
to be my girlfriend

41:39.279 --> 41:41.063
because I have autism?

41:49.376 --> 41:51.421
Mmm. [SIGHS]

41:58.298 --> 42:00.213
[SIGHS SHAKILY]

42:02.911 --> 42:04.652
[SIGHS]

42:08.047 --> 42:09.657
[SIGHS]

42:09.701 --> 42:11.441
[FOOTSTEPS FADE]

42:16.098 --> 42:17.883
[DOOR OPENS]

42:20.625 --> 42:22.670
[DOOR CLOSES]

42:31.113 --> 42:34.726
